# Backend API Configuration
VITE_BACKEND_API=https://oscontribackend.onrender.com

# GitHub API Configuration
VITE_GITHUB_API=https://api.github.com
VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token_here

# How to get a GitHub Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to GitHub.com → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic)
# 2. Click "Generate new token" → "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Add a note like "Open Source Tracker App"
# 4. Select the following scopes:
#    - public_repo (Access public repositories)
#    - read:user (Read user profile information)
# 5. Copy the token and paste it above (replace "your_github_personal_access_token_here")
# 6. Rename this file to .env (remove .example)

# Note: GitHub API rate limits:
# - Without token: 60 requests per hour
# - With token: 5,000 requests per hour 